<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/52334154-blue">Blue</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes and no, depends on the kid. It is not a book that was written for kids. <br/><br/>I think I read this in 5th or 6th grade. My brothers read it at a similar <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes and no, depends on the kid. It is not a book that was written for kids. <br /><br />I think I read this in 5th or 6th grade. My brothers read it at a similar age and both liked it. I enjoyed it as a kid and was eager to read the sequel. Rereading it as an adult though was almost like reading a whole different book. ;) <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
