<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/377190-i-was-wondering-if-the-books-follow-on-or">I was wondering if the books follow on or can I say start at book seven?
 As I get most of my books from the Library I cant get them in order.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_377190'><a id="like_count_community_question_377190" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/377190?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">10 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F34497.The_Color_of_Magic">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/377190-i-was-wondering-if-the-books-follow-on-or">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/377190-i-was-wondering-if-the-books-follow-on-or">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/21463378-ekaterina-spitsyna"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1422753346i/21463378._UY100_CR3,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/21463378-ekaterina-spitsyna">Ekaterina Spitsyna</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think you should look up recommended order to read the books, to know approximately where you are standing. (like this one: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.lspace.org/books/reading-order-guides/the-discworld-reading-order-guide-20.jpg'>http://www.lspace.org/bo</a><a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think you should look up recommended order to read the books, to know approximately where you are standing. (like this one: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.lspace.org/books/reading-order-guides/the-discworld-reading-order-guide-20.jpg">http://www.lspace.org/books/reading-o...</a>)<br />And basically, you can read them in any order, as the author keeps reminding you of important, and not so important, details, and as the books are just brilliant enough by themselves.<br />Of course, it would be a bit harder to keep up with the timeline, and you won't be very surprised with the ending if you have already read the next book, but it won't ruin the impression or fun.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

